<task id="107" project="spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>PCF build + deploy via `/pcf-deploy`; remove obsolete `searchIndexName` text bindings on Main forms</title>
    <phase>G: Lookup-driven multi-index</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>1-2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>106</dependencies>
    <blocks>110</blocks>
    <tags>pcf, deploy, dataverse-form</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Deploy + maker UI changes. No new code logic; invokes canonical pcf-deploy skill.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Sequential after 106 — needs the v1.1.75 artifact.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build + deploy PCF v1.1.75 via the canonical `/pcf-deploy` skill (clean rebuild + 5-loc version verify + solution pack + Dataverse import + publish). Then, for each Main form that has the SemanticSearch PCF instance (Matter, Project, Invoice, Event, WorkAssignment), open the PCF control properties pane and REMOVE the obsolete `searchIndexName` bound property binding (the property no longer exists in v1.1.75; the form-instance binding would be a no-op but it should be cleaned up explicitly). Save + publish each form.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Dataverse maker + PCF deployer. Familiar with the `/pcf-deploy` skill and Power Apps form editor.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `sprk_Sprk.SemanticSearchControl` v1.1.75 deployed and published in `spaarkedev1.crm.dynamics.com`. All Main forms that host the PCF have their (now-orphaned) `searchIndexName` text binding removed. Forms saved + published.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>.claude/skills/pcf-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/Solution/pack.ps1</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/notes/phase-g/spec.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source=".claude/skills/pcf-deploy/SKILL.md">Clean rebuild MANDATORY (rm -rf out/ + npm run build:prod). 5-location version verification BEFORE pack. ZIP entry names lowercase. `pac solution import` with `--publish-changes`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-10">Stale `dist/` of `@spaarke/auth` or `@spaarke/ui-components` poisons bundle — rebuild those FIRST if their src changed since last PCF build. (Not expected for this task; verify nonetheless.)</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md §5">Form-level cleanup: remove obsolete bindings on Matter / Project / Invoice / Event / WorkAssignment Main forms.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/skills/pcf-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/PCF-DEPLOYMENT-GUIDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/notes/phase-g/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Verify @spaarke/ui-components + @spaarke/auth dist/ are up to date relative to src/ (run `npm run build` in each shared lib only if src is newer than dist).</step>
    <step order="2">Invoke `/pcf-deploy` skill OR follow the procedure: `rm -rf out/ bin/`, `npm run build:prod`, copy bundle.js + ControlManifest.xml + styles.css from out/ to Solution/Controls/sprk_Sprk.SemanticSearchControl/, `cd Solution && powershell -File pack.ps1`, `pac solution import --path Solution/bin/SpaarkeSemanticSearch_v1.1.75.zip --publish-changes`.</step>
    <step order="3">Verify control footer shows "v1.1.75" in a browser hard-refresh of any form hosting the control.</step>
    <step order="4">For each of the 5 Main forms (Matter, Project, Invoice, Event, WorkAssignment): open form in Power Apps maker → click the SemanticSearch PCF control → in right pane Properties, locate any "Search Index Name" property (will appear as obsolete/unbound under v1.1.75) and remove it. Save + Publish.</step>
    <step order="5">Hard-refresh a model-driven app + open a Matter; verify the PCF loads without console errors and that the new lookup-driven path is used (App Insights or browser dev-tools network tab confirms the BFF request body carries `searchIndexName` matching the Matter's `sprk_aisearchindexid` row).</step>
    <step order="6">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 107 🔲 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Bash">npm run build:prod, pack.ps1, pac solution import</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">Optional: kusto query App Insights to confirm searchIndexName routing</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="artifact">SpaarkeSemanticSearch_v1.1.75.zip imported and published</output>
    <output type="config">5 Main forms cleaned of obsolete searchIndexName binding</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`pac solution list | grep SpaarkeSemanticSearch` shows v1.1.75.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Browser hard-refresh on a form shows "v1.1.75" footer.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Opening a Matter w/ `sprk_aisearchindexid` set fires `/api/ai/search` with `searchIndexName: &lt;the looked-up name&gt;` in the request body (verifiable in browser Network tab).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All 5 Main forms saved + published with no orphan `searchIndexName` binding.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <deploy-skill>.claude/skills/pcf-deploy/SKILL.md</deploy-skill>
  </execution>
</task>
